{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend ban on smoking in indoor public places to e-cigarettes and fund research",
        "additional_details": "Although the vapour released from vaping is believed to be much less toxic than from normal cigarettes, the vapours are still able to \"fill up\" a room and can create a haze in a pub or club or other such venue and the vapours can still induce coughing from others who breathe it in. \r\nhttps://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/28/contents",
        "background": "The Government should extend the ban on indoor smoking of cigarettes to also include e-cigarettes/vaping. The Government should also fund more research to determine the long-term effects of these vapours.",
